com.sensorstack.AAlayer

Class AALayerII

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.sensorstack.AAlayer.AALayerII

  • public class AALayerII
extends java.lang.Object
    This layer manages AALayer-I. The application layer must invoke calls to this layer for fetching medical data from the sensors (i.e. without any metadata). Note - If you need metadata along with medical data, you must invoke the provenance layer class methods instead, see ProvenanceLayer

      • STANDARD_TEMPERATURE_RANGE

        public static final RangeOfValues<java.lang.Float> STANDARD_TEMPERATURE_RANGE
        Defines standard range for Temperature sensor. The values obtained from the hardware as the the hardware data range are mapped to this range before getting returned. The application layer should expect data from any temperature sensor having values mapped to this range.

      • setHardwareRange

        public static void setHardwareRange(SensorDataRange range)
        Hardware Range defines the valid range for the sensor hardware. This object is initialised with standard range for each of the sensors. This function allows user to set this range. If the range passed for a sensor is null, previous value is retained.
        Parameters:
        range - specify range for different sensors
